    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>white potato[es] </strong>and <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>,<strong> </strong>then give it a good mix up<strong> </strong>and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1641303003324-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1641303003324-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1641303003324-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1641303003324-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1641303003324-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> radishes </strong>(as finely as you can)</p><p>Combine your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>in a large bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot </strong>and <strong>sliced radish </strong>to the bowl, give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1641303006517-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1641303006517-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1641303006517-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1641303006517-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1641303006517-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a splash of <strong>milk</strong> to a shallow bowl</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and<strong> half </strong>your <strong>curry powder </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a plate and season with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1641303010109-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1641303010109-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1641303010109-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1641303010109-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1641303010109-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Coat your <strong>chicken breast</strong> <strong>portion[s]</strong> in the <strong>flour mixture</strong>, tap off the excess, then add to the <strong>milk</strong> and finally press into the <strong>panko</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p><p>Tip: If your chicken is a bit too thick, slice it in half horizontally so you’re left with two thinner pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1641303014145-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1641303014145-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1641303014145-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1641303014145-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1641303014145-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken</strong> and cook for 8 min on each side, pressing down firmly with a spatula until the outside is golden and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>chicken katsu</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641303018506-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641303018506-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641303018506-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641303018506-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1641303018506-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and stir for 30 secs, then transfer the <strong>curried butter</strong> to a bowl to cool</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Put your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> in the oven for 5 min or until hot and crusty</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1641303021739-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1641303021739-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1641303021739-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1641303021739-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1641303021739-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the liquid from the <strong>quick-pickled slaw </strong>and add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Stir your <strong>mayo</strong>,<strong> mango chutney </strong>and<strong> white wine vinegar </strong>into the <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>curried butter </strong>– this is your <strong>curried mayo</strong></p><p>Carefully slice the <strong>warmed ciabatta[s] </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1641303024858-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1641303024858-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1641303024858-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1641303024858-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1641303024858-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To assemble, spread the <strong>warmed ciabatta base </strong>with some of the <strong>curried mayo</strong>, then top with the <strong>chicken katsu</strong>, some <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong>, another dollop of <strong>curried mayo </strong>and<strong> </strong>the <strong>warmed ciabatta lid </strong>– this is your<strong> chicken katsu burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>fries</strong> and any <strong>remaining quick-pickled slaw</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
